    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The shift position sensor is fixed to the transmission control shaft. The control shaft rotates via the control wire when the driver operates the select lever. The shift position indicator shows which position is selected by the LO/HI signal from the angle of rotation of the control shaft. In addition to operating the shift position sensor, the control shaft also switches the hydraulic pressure of the transmission between forward/neutral/reverse by operating a manual valve. The PGM-FI ECU uses the signal from the shift position sensor to determine the gear shift schedule. The input terminal voltage of the PGM-FI ECU is HI when each switch in the shift position sensor is open and LO when closed. When the select lever is operated in the P, R, or N position, if the RVS switch signal is open (HI) in the R position, the PGM-FI ECU judges a failure and stores a DTC."
    },
