    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Failure Criteria"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If the RVS signal [reverse SW] is not detected for 0.32 seconds in the R position when the select lever is operated in the P, R, or N position."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Estimated Failure Site"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Disconnection of the cord (ATP-RVS line) between the PGM-FI ECU and the shift position sensor (including disconnected or loose coupler)"
        },
        {
          "text": "Poor adjustment of control wires"
        },
        {
          "text": "Shift position sensor failure"
        },
        {
          "text": "PGM-FI ECU internal circuit failure"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Reproducibility Testing Methodology"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Start the engine."
        },
        {
          "text": "Operate the select lever in the P, R, and N positions, and wait in the R position for at least 0.32 seconds."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "None."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Store and clear DTC"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If the vehicle is determined to have a fault, a temporary DTC is stored in the PGM-FI ECU memory. If the same failure is detected at the next D/C (two consecutive detections), the D indicator light will flash without the PGM-FI warning light illuminating, and the DTC and freeze data will be stored."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Use of the clear command of the scan tool (including HDS) or removal of the 12V battery terminal will clear the D indicator light, temporary DTC, DTC, and freeze data."
    }
